name: 08 - Lesson 2 - Main Text.mp3
format: mp3
duration: 02:00.529
id: 35ede59c-a247-4264-87a9-48fd686d75b6
clips:
  - id: cf4aacab-af53-4caa-a5e9-14881f5ae69f
    start: 00:06.22
    end: 00:12.0
    fields:
      transcription: 人間の手はいろいろなことをするが、足のほうはあまり働かない。
      meaning: "Although the human hand performs many functions, our feet hardly do any work at all. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: cdb0f1aa-ba95-4dbc-8528-049ef264ad58
    start: 00:12.44
    end: 00:16.62
    fields:
      transcription: 歩くことと走ることのほかは大した仕事をしない。
      meaning: Apart from walking and running, their workload is scant.
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: c4e213ba-920f-4b99-9c46-ac20883e0288
    start: 00:17.18
    end: 00:22.58
    fields:
      transcription: 特に足のうらは何も重要な働きはしていないように見える。
      meaning: " Whats more, the backs of our feet perform scarcely any major function. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: 108e31d1-fae5-4955-a906-e0b194e1f337
    start: 00:23.12
    end: 00:29.7
    fields:
      transcription: ところが、足のうらの働きについて実験した結果、面白いことがわかったそうだ。
      meaning: "Or so it had seemed, until a series of experiments on their activity came up with some interesting results. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: a22d94ee-8959-4248-807b-5e9f497624ba
    start: 00:30.8
    end: 00:34.66
    fields:
      transcription: 十二人の若い男女を二つの組にわける。
      meaning: "Twelve men and women, all of them young, were divided into two groups. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: afa843b9-a206-4b70-b9cf-a151a470afaa
    start: 00:35.2
    end: 00:41.38
    fields:
      transcription: 一定の時間、いっぽう組の人たちは、はだしになって竹をふみ続ける。
      meaning: "After taking off their shoes, the first group repeatedly stamped their feet on strips of bamboo for a specified period of time. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: fac39827-01e9-4ad8-b0ca-59924f624206
    start: 00:41.72
    end: 00:47.1
    fields:
      transcription: もういっぽうの組は、高いいすにこしかけて、何もしないでいる
      meaning: "The second group simply sat motionless on a tall chair. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: feecb4b5-2987-43b3-94c5-103cd32cffce
    start: 00:47.9
    end: 00:54.64
    fields:
      transcription: いすが高いので、足はゆかにつかないから、足のうらには何の刺激もない。
      meaning: "The chair's height prevented their feet from touching the ground—and kept the backs of their feet from receiving any stimulus. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: 708aafbb-234f-4236-9a2c-fb197574fc36
    start: 00:55.26
    end: 00:59.12
    fields:
      transcription: そのあと両方の組が同じゲームをする。
      meaning: "Later, the two groups took part in a game. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: 833e3e3d-dbf8-44d5-b294-5f5eb33c9016
    start: 00:59.6
    end: 01:09.1
    fields:
      transcription: テレビの画面に色の名前を表す漢字が出るが、その漢字の表す色と、漢字そのものの色はちがっている。
      meaning: "The names of colors were shown in kanji on a video monitor. The kanji were displayed in colors that differed from their meaning; "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: f298e99a-238e-422e-9c57-b1c68e104869
    start: 01:09.46
    end: 01:13.34
    fields:
      transcription: たとえば白い線で書いた「青」という字が出る。
      meaning: 'For example, the character for "blue" was drawn with white lines. '
      notes: jí-ga déru
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: 56d57479-6c2d-4fce-9192-a8fb0c0f3532
    start: 01:13.9
    end: 01:18.28
    fields:
      transcription: それを見て、いそいで「青」の札をさがして高くあげる。
      meaning: "After looking at the kanji for blue, the groups had to hastily search for a card displaying it, then raise this card high in the air. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: 53df8e93-daaf-424e-a654-4f31abe161c9
    start: 01:18.78
    end: 01:28.48
    fields:
      transcription: 何回も続けると、疲れて間違いが多くなるが、二つの組のうち、竹をふんだ人達のほうが成績がよかった。
      meaning: "After many attempts, the groups grew tired, and their mistakes multiplied. Yet the performance of the group that had stamped its feet on the bamboo was best. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: a6941968-0cde-4337-80a3-e40535a19fa2
    start: 01:28.82
    end: 01:35.22
    fields:
      transcription: つまり足のうらを刺激すると、頭の働きがよくなることがわかったのである。
      meaning: "The experiment convinced its designers that, by stimulating the backs of our feet, we can upgrade the performance of our brains. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: bea710d1-472b-4faf-aa60-ec3685db945b
    start: 01:36.16
    end: 01:51.72
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        むかしのある有名な人は、子供のころ家がびんぼうで、一日中働いていたので、勉強するひまがなかった。
        そこで、せなかに薪をせおって歩きながら、本を読んだそうである。
      meaning: "A famous person of old used to read while walking with a load of firewood on his back. As a child, his family was poor, and he had to work from dawn to dusk—leaving scarcely any time for study. "
    tags:
      - iij02
  - id: 091a8350-b944-4e64-8818-e4dd3fe0c523
    start: 01:52.2
    end: 02:00.0
    fields:
      transcription: 目のためには悪かったかもしれないが、頭の働きのためには、よい勉強法だったわけである。
      meaning: The child's study technique was undoubtedly bad for his eyesight. Yet for improving the performance of his mind, it was unexcelled.
    tags:
      - iij02
