name: 15 - Lesson 3 - Main Text.mp3
format: mp3
duration: 02:00.921
id: 9b3fc3ac-aeec-46ea-8ec7-b55c39add913
clips:
  - id: 2a79c166-cae6-4dd7-9302-c57100c1071c
    start: 00:05.86
    end: 00:12.92
    fields:
      transcription: 留守番電話を利用する人が多くなった。留守番電話は確かに便利である。
      meaning: "A growing number of people are starting to use answering machines. Without a doubt, the answering machine is a handy instrument. "
      notes: bénri
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 617e425d-1e2a-46a9-b49f-463a7feb78c5
    start: 00:13.26
    end: 00:21.92
    fields:
      transcription: 誰も家にいない時に誰から電話があった場合、後で録音テープでその内容を知ることができる。
      meaning: "If the phone rings when everybody's out of the house, it's now possible to hear the content of the call afterwards on tape. "
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: bc802300-72be-447e-a778-09add27c5ce6
    start: 00:22.44
    end: 00:28.86
    fields:
      transcription: "家にいる時でも、風呂に入っていたりして、電話に出ることができないこともある。 "
      meaning: "At home, there are times, such as in the middle of a bath, when picking up the phone is impossible. "
      notes: Ié-ni iru tokí-de-mo, furó-ni háitte itári shite, denwa-ni déru-koto-ga dekínai-koto-mo áru.
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 366e8d12-2c0d-4d96-8730-4031cb4ecd8c
    start: 00:29.62
    end: 00:38.64
    fields:
      transcription: 例えば、食事中やテレビで面白いドラマを見ている時など、電話にでなくて済むのはありがたいことである。
      meaning: "What's more, not having to answer the phone during a meal—or an interesting television drama—is a blessing. "
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 852bf3d7-bdcd-452d-8ec3-7e2e8fa2f7fd
    start: 00:39.86
    end: 00:44.72
    fields:
      transcription: それほど便利なものであるが、つけたくないと言う人も多い。
      meaning: "For a device that's so convenient, a surprising number of people don't want to use the answering machine. "
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: a36bb160-1591-47b3-b571-eb5fcc22c080
    start: 00:45.1
    end: 00:52.02
    fields:
      transcription: 電話をかけたとき、相手の声でなく録音テープを聞くのが不ゆかいなためである。
      meaning: "They feel that it's unpleasant to listen to a tape rather than the actual voice of the person they are calling. "
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 05661bf5-d536-4418-b33a-491025caf020
    start: 00:52.74
    end: 01:07.18
    fields:
      transcription: 「いま留守です。ピーという音の後で、ご用件をお話しください」と言う事務的な声を聞くのが嫌いだし、人にもそんな声を聞かせたくない、と言う人が多い。
      meaning: Many people can't stand to hear a perfunctory voice say "I'm not home right now, but when you hear the tone, please leave a message"—and don't want to force this remark on the people who call them.
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: ce61275d-909b-436f-9c73-65d241f4b4b9
    start: 01:08.0
    end: 01:17.76
    fields:
      transcription: 留守番電話の伝言にしたがって電話してみると、その人も留守番電話をつけているので、録音テープに話をする。
      meaning: "If, following the instructions on your answering machine, you call back the other party, you often find your- self speaking into the answering machine owned by that person. "
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 35be6ac4-7913-4675-80ac-7534eebaf251
    start: 01:18.22
    end: 01:22.48
    fields:
      transcription: その返事もまた録音テープということもある。
      meaning: "The reply to your message, in turn, is often recorded into your machine. "
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 61457ee0-70ba-42ea-bd17-7f2e762382f9
    start: 01:22.86
    end: 01:29.08
    fields:
      transcription: こうなると、人と話すのでなく、いつもマイクにむかって話すことになる。
      meaning: "As a result, telephoners end up feeling like they're talking to microphones rather than to each other. "
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 8350aa7c-cbae-4720-ba28-b83f4ec84b25
    start: 01:29.28
    end: 01:34.66
    fields:
      transcription: 普通の人も、テレビやラジオのアナウンサーになったようなものだ。
      meaning: "It's almost as if ordinary people had suddenly become TV or radio announcers. "
      notes: 〜ようなものだ = it's as if...
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: c6123f52-e629-481d-bf38-b11595fe1f07
    start: 01:35.46
    end: 01:44.26
    fields:
      transcription: 話しかけてすぐ返事を聞くことができるのが、電話の魅力であるが、留守番電話ではそれがない。
      meaning: "The appeal of the telephone lies in hearing an immediate reply after speaking to someone. Answering machines don't have this advantage. "
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: 2cb15b95-42c0-4bfb-bf7c-eaceb44c6d35
    start: 01:44.52
    end: 01:49.66
    fields:
      transcription: 手紙を受け取って読んで、返事を書いて送るのと似ている。
      meaning: "[Using an answering machine] is somewhat like receiving a letter, reading its contents, then writing and mailing a reply."
      notes: uketotte yónde
    tags:
      - iij03
  - id: df49690f-ec0a-4d94-ad6c-850f3813f634
    start: 01:49.82
    end: 02:00.38
    fields:
      transcription: もちろんその速さは手紙と比較にならないが、同時性がないという点では、手紙時代に逆もどりしたような気がする。
      meaning: "As for the speed of the response, letters don't compare with answering machines. Nonetheless, answering machines can't offer the immediacy [of the telephone]: and [it seems to me that] they've taken us back to an age of letter writing as a result."
    tags:
      - iij03
