name: 07 - Lesson 9 - Main Text.mp3
format: mp3
duration: 01:53.554
id: 7b500308-c3d3-4516-a2b8-7c4a7a068384
subtitles:
  - id: d20c34f6-4e2b-4279-8d79-049c56b4ea1d
    type: External
    chunksMetadata:
      count: 29
      endCue: 5619.2
    name: 07 - Lesson 9 - Main Text.srt
clips:
  - id: 01881d9b-a273-4e4e-bd85-e098affad332
    start: 00:06.54
    end: 00:14.26
    fields:
      transcription: 電話をすれば家まで荷物を取りに来て、1日か2日のうちに 全国どこへでも届ける。
      meaning: With a single phone call, it’s now possible to have a parcel picked up at one's home and delivered a day or two later to a location anywhere in Japan.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: ca437f9c-6a7d-48af-917b-bfd13f943c5f
    start: 00:14.52
    end: 00:17.72
    fields:
      transcription: こういう宅配便がこの頃増えている。
      meaning: Home delivery agencies offering services like these are on the rise.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 9b35684f-290d-400e-a3ed-c8f15c72be51
    start: 00:18.1
    end: 00:23.56
    fields:
      transcription: 利用する立場からは実に便利だが届ける人は大変であろう。
      meaning: From the client’s perspective, such services are convenient indeed—but they must be hard on the deliverer.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 802ea9c3-58b5-4dd3-a15a-c723ab88bb1a
    start: 00:24.392
    end: 00:30.32
    fields:
      transcription: ある大きな宅配便の会社の例を数日前テレビで紹介していた。
      meaning: An example of one of the larger home delivery firms was presented on television a few days back.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: bd448257-2a0d-4202-baaf-1fe6f1f661cf
    start: 00:30.612
    end: 00:36.952
    fields:
      transcription: この会社では最近、コンピューターで社員のトラックの動きを記録することにした。
      meaning: The firm recently started using a computer to record the movements of its delivery vans.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 8bfdee66-08a5-46d3-8ec8-33fe39954dd7
    start: 00:37.332
    end: 00:43.432
    fields:
      transcription: 事務所のコンピューターに、何時何分にどこを通ったか、全部記録される。
      meaning: Its office's computer records the position of each van down to the minute.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 5de4f3cf-c7ee-4210-afe6-dbcb87fba5b3
    start: 00:43.692
    end: 00:47.432
    fields:
      transcription: 運転手にとっては大変なプレッシャーであろう。
      meaning: One can imagine the intense pressure the drivers must be under.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 09a62149-b291-4208-8b78-5ab9e3535268
    start: 00:47.872
    end: 00:54.0
    fields:
      transcription: しかも運転席のそばの機械が事務所からの指令を次々に打ち出す。
      meaning: To make matters worse, a machine beside the driver's seat makes a continuous print-out of new instructions from the company.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 6f36fa3f-edfc-4199-8d97-36bfa26c5b24
    start: 00:54.312
    end: 00:58.872
    fields:
      transcription: 車を停めて荷物を届けに行っている間にも指令が来る。
      meaning: The instructions pour out of the machine even when the driver has stopped the van to deliver a parcel.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 52bb5ce6-dc80-4916-917e-f2871d01ecb4
    start: 00:59.252
    end: 01:11.492
    fields:
      transcription: 以前は運転手が車にいない時は指令を送ることができないので、注文を断っていたが、今度の方法で注文を受ける数が多いに増えたそうである。
      meaning: Home delivery companies were formerly unable to convey instructions to their drivers when they were out of the van, forcing them to turn down orders from clients. This new technique has dra- matically increased the numbers of orders that the companies can handle.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 52ad117b-8c20-424b-ae6c-eda8492d2ca5
    start: 01:12.212
    end: 01:17.192
    fields:
      transcription: しかし、働く人の仕事も増え、疲れもひどくなる。
      meaning: Nonetheless. the workloads of their employees have increased, and on-the-job fatigue is severe.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 25738df7-d07a-434e-b6d5-00a468f2542f
    start: 01:17.432
    end: 01:20.312
    fields:
      transcription: 途中でやめる社員も多いそうだ。
      meaning: Many employees have quit their jobs.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: ae0bd1f1-85f5-44ae-b04b-878e7586506d
    start: 01:20.652
    end: 01:31.292
    fields:
      transcription: 人間と機械の組み合わせは難しい。人間が機械を使うのでなく、機械が人間を使うことになってしまう場合も多い
      meaning: Combining humans and machines is difficult; in many instances, the worker becomes used by the machine, rather than the reverse.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 5b108bf5-fa27-417c-aad3-803bd788583b
    start: 01:31.832
    end: 01:42.08
    fields:
      transcription: これだけコンピューターが進歩したのだから、トラックも無人にしてコンピューターで動かし、荷物はロボットが運ぶようにしたらどうだろう。
      meaning: Since computers have improved so tremendously, why not put them in charge of a driverless van—and have a robot deliver the packages?
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 3bddc73e-c7d5-44bb-a962-bda2e4767814
    start: 01:42.272
    end: 01:52.812
    fields:
      transcription: ピンポーンと鳴ったので玄関へ出てみると、黒猫のロボットが立っていて、お菓子の箱を差し出すなんて、想像すると楽しいではないか。
      meaning: It's fun to imagine answering the doorbell and discovering a box of sweets delivered by a robotized black cat.
    tags:
      - iij09
