name: 19 - Lesson 11 - Main Text.mp3
format: mp3
duration: 02:09.985
id: 2438c349-06f9-4ad9-b092-26406c93f6ce
subtitles:
  - id: 23796937-9232-4158-9bd0-8766e2f2f383
    type: External
    chunksMetadata:
      count: 37
      endCue: 6297.6
    name: 19 - Lesson 11 - Main Text.srt
clips:
  - id: 9a48e2f2-59e3-4f4d-8ebf-ce7a3d1fe6a3
    start: 00:05.92
    end: 00:09.74
    fields:
      transcription: ゴミの処理は多くの国で問題になっている
      meaning: The disposal of garbage has become a problem in many countries.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 0d1ca109-f12f-4e6b-8528-ca4fec937209
    start: 00:10.38
    end: 00:14.76
    fields:
      transcription: 他の国にゴミを運んで処理を頼む場合もあるそうだ
      meaning: Some places are even transporting their trash to other countries for disposal.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 854262cb-0e87-4085-8848-87eadce55e65
    start: 00:15.46
    end: 00:29.2
    fields:
      transcription: 日本でも最近、関東地方のある県が、遠く東北地方にまでゴミを運んで処理を頼んだが、話し合いがうまくいかなくて、まだ問題は解決していない そうである。
      meaning: A certain prefecture in the Kanto region ofJapan has shipped its garbage to the remote Tohoku area; discussions with officials in the area haven’t gone as expected and the problem remains unresolved.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 821e42d5-3057-4628-95c3-ea2e2004b520
    start: 00:29.82
    end: 00:40.08
    fields:
      transcription: 特にビニールやプラスチックのゴミは処理が難しく、地中に埋めることが多いが、埋める場所も限界に近づいている。
      meaning: Vinyl and plastics are particularly hard to get rid of. Though both of these substances are usually buried in the ground, disposal sites are approaching a limit.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 4e7038cf-a74d-45c3-8eff-a1c93f6e11fd
    start: 00:40.98
    end: 00:53.22
    fields:
      transcription: 最近の「広報東京都」に、「各家庭から出るコミは、一人ひとりのちょっとした努力と気遣いで減らすことができます」という記事が出ていた。
      meaning: “With a little effort and attentiveness on the part of individuals," claimed an article in a recent issue of The Tokyo Information, “the garbage produced by households can be decreased.”
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 8f8d830a-ae9a-4d06-867c-03383f8a1857
    start: 00:53.92
    end: 01:00.28
    fields:
      transcription: また、今朝の新聞には、北海道のある町の場合についての投書が出ていた。
      meaning: This morning’s paper ran a letter on garbage disposal in a city in Hokkaido. 
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 3aab282f-ef0e-4fdc-a72c-b5d59f73e4c5
    start: 01:01.16
    end: 01:08.46
    fields:
      transcription: ゴミを出す時は乾電池、生ゴミ、固形燃料など六種類に分けて出す。
      meaning: "The city segregates its garbage into six types—batteries; food: solid fuels—before disposal."
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 23195efc-3a71-477a-b2ba-2b9e4888ec0a
    start: 01:08.86
    end: 01:13.08
    fields:
      transcription: 乾電池は市中の数か所にあるポストに捨てる。
      meaning: Batteries are dropped into receptacles in several places in the city.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 1594b8d3-e377-4f87-9280-7677301d2088
    start: 01:13.5
    end: 01:19.54
    fields:
      transcription: 生ゴミは処理して、老人のための施設で燃料として使うそうである。
      meaning: Food is reconverted into fuel for institutions for the elderly.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 62c2c392-069b-40bb-a899-5ec9e8e57c3d
    start: 01:20.2
    end: 01:28.32
    fields:
      transcription: 「ゴミを細かく分けて出すのは最初は面倒でも、そのうちに慣れてしまいます」と投書者は言う。
      meaning: “Minutely segregating garbage is a nuisance at first,” said the letter-writer. “But you get used to it after a while."
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 36a28c30-9c67-45c1-b73c-be47cf0a76a4
    start: 01:28.8
    end: 01:36.5
    fields:
      transcription: このような捨て方の工夫も大切であるが、ゴミをあまり出さないようにすることも必要であろう。
      meaning: Thinking of ways like these to dispose of waste is important. Yet it’s also necessary to conserve on the garbage that we already throw away.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: edf2b5cc-6bcd-4bad-91a2-dd6c4da46870
    start: 01:37.02
    end: 01:41.28
    fields:
      transcription: 買い物をするたびに包み紙を捨てなければならない。
      meaning: Shopping trips always result in wrapping paper that needs to be disposed.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 6ef3970d-eb82-4e58-9360-0219444b133e
    start: 01:41.78
    end: 01:51.86
    fields:
      transcription: 贈り物をもらうと綺麗な包み紙の中にまた箱や感があって、結局、中のものと同じくらいのゴミが出る。
      meaning: Presents are wrapped with elegant paper and contained in a box or can; we end up throwing away trash that's equivalent in volume to the present.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: b07e6178-a9c4-4f56-9a75-7bdbf323278e
    start: 01:52.26
    end: 01:57.76
    fields:
      transcription: しかし、綺麗な包み紙がなければ、商品は売れないのが現実だ。
      meaning: Yet products wouldn't sell were it not for their elegant wrapping paper.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: 834963c3-873d-4e14-8823-8ef39c3ee8db
    start: 01:58.5
    end: 02:02.14
    fields:
      transcription: 「一人ひとりの努力」だけでは不十分である。
      meaning: “Effort on the part of individuals” isn’t enough.
    tags:
      - iij11
  - id: b32f52c9-6a82-4988-8d7a-97ea4d507a0d
    start: 02:02.74
    end: 02:09.6
    fields:
      transcription: 商品の流通機構そのものを変えなければ、ゴミ問題の解決にはならないであろう。
      meaning: "If we don’t revise our system of distributing goods. it’s unlikely that a solution will ever be found to the problem of waste disposal. "
    tags:
      - iij11
